data.description: Nestled within minutes of Boulder, Longmont, Denver, and Fort Collins, this exceptional property spans over 10 acres and is a sanctuary for nature enthusiasts. Backing onto the serene Wild Bird Sanctuary and positioned along Boulder Creek, it offers a tranquil retreat. Situated in a quiet cul-de-sac, this haven boasts 5 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, including a walkout basement with two full kitchens, perfect for multifamily living or rental opportunities.The main level features an inviting open floor plan with wood floors and a wood-burning fireplace in the living room, creating a cozy ambiance. The walkout basement offers a wood stove in the living area. A detached, heated 2-car garage complements the property, providing ample space for vehicles or a workshop.For those inclined to sustainable living, there's a chicken coop, a horse barn with 3 stalls and runs, and electric fences surrounding the property. Adding to its charm, peacocks grace the landscape. Beyond its residential appeal, the property offers subdividable potential, inviting the creation of a family compound with up to 4 additional houses.This property invites creativity, whether exploring business ventures or utilizing the vast acreage for personalized projects. Seize the opportunity to craft your dream home or capitalize on diverse business prospects amidst this natural paradise. Seller offering $45,000 for a rate buy down!
